olive oil
1 cucumber
½ lemon
1 packet salmon
2 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
½ tbs plain flour
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet Asian Slaw Mix
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet mayonnaise
1 tsp sesame oil
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet mint

• Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons. Slice lemon into wedges.
• Pat salmon dry with paper towel.
• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add salmon and gently turn to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add sweet chilli sauce and a squeeze of lemon juice. Gently turn salmon to coat.

• In a large bowl, combine Asian slaw mix, cucumber, baby leaves,
mayonnaise, the sesame oil, a squeeze of lemon juice and a pinch of salt.

• Divide Asian slaw between bowls.
• Top with sweet chilli fish, along with any remaining glaze.
• Sprinkle over crushed peanuts and tear over mint to serve. Enjoy!